    • getElementsCount

      public int getElementsCount(IInteractableNaming identifier)
      Returns the count of elements that match the provided identifier. This method checks if the identifier is of type SELECTOR, and if so, it returns the number of elements found by the given selector. If the identifier type is not SELECTOR, it logs a warning and returns 0.
      Specified by:
      getElementsCount in interface ICoreCssControl
      Parameters:
      identifier - The identifier used to find the elements.
      Returns:

    • getTextFromElements

      public List<String> getTextFromElements(IInteractableNaming identifier)
      Returns the text from all elements that match the provided identifier. This method checks if the identifier is of type SELECTOR, and if so, it retrieves the text of all elements found by the given selector. If the identifier type is not SELECTOR, it logs a warning and returns an empty list.
      Specified by:
      getTextFromElements in interface ICoreCssControl
      Parameters:
      identifier - The identifier used to find the elements.
      Returns:
      A list of text from all matching elements.

    • getPropertyOfPseudoElement

      public String getPropertyOfPseudoElement(String id, PseudoElement pElement, String property)
      Retrieves the specified CSS property value of a pseudo-element of an HTML element. This method uses JavaScript to access the computed style of a pseudo-element (e.g., ::before, ::after) of the HTML element identified by the provided id. It executes a JavaScript script to retrieve the property value for the given pseudo-element and property name. If an error occurs (e.g., if the WebDriver is not available or if the element is not found), it logs the error. If no value is retrieved, it returns an empty string.
      Specified by:
      getPropertyOfPseudoElement in interface ICoreCssControl
      Parameters:
      id - The ID of the HTML element.
      pElement - The pseudo-element (e.g., ::before, ::after).
      property - The CSS property whose value is to be retrieved.
      Returns:
      The value of the specified CSS property for the pseudo-element, or an empty string if an error occurs.
